ck here, just need to keep that environment in mind!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- Added `tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/LexerFrameTest.groovy`\n\nThe test exercises `org.codehaus.groovy.antlr.LexerFrame` through its Swing file-open flow using `GroovyLexer` and `GroovyTokenTypes`, which should reach:\n\n- `LexerFrame.listTokens(...)`\n  - `Class#getDeclaredFields`\n  - `Field#get`\n- `LexerFrame.scanScript(...)`\n  - `Class#getConstructor`\n  - `Constructor#newInstance`\n\nIt uses bounded waits and disposes all AWT windows after execution.\n\nPer instruction, I did not run/compile the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0359bec474ff1a75016a273399926481939df719041980f93e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 824, "output": 725, "cacheRead": 61952, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63501, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780953994882, "responseId": "resp_0359bec474ff1a75016a27338bbf4c8193baba1ff4cf9fa04f"}, "toolResults": []}
